summary: Pokemon Shuffle Patches for clips!  I'd had this idea in my mind for quite a while, and decided it was time to go forward with...
caption:
Pokemon Shuffle Patches for clips!

I’d had this idea in my mind for quite a while, and decided it was time to go forward with it. Yesterday I finished digitizing a few patterns for some of my favs- Mimikyu, Oddish, and Snorlax, in order to make these cute hair clips. This was my first real experimentation with applique on my embroidery machine, and there was a def learning curve involved (especially with Oddish) but I think I got it!

And yes! These will be made available in my Etsy store once I get the clips done and price them out entirely. I’ll also offer them as small patches, and if I find good backings, regular pins as well.

summary: I’ve already uploaded the Sylveon but I thought that I’d upload the dump that I just put together of my recent Pokémon...
caption:
I’ve already uploaded the Sylveon but I thought that I’d upload the dump that I just put together of my recent Pokémon drawings! 

Arcanine has those accessories as a reference to my character Dom. This firey boy would definitely be his mascot! 

The numbers are there because I offered short descriptions for each on DeviantART. I didn’t have much to say about these, but here’s the link if you want it: https://www.deviantart.com/purplesallyjay/art/Sketch-dump-Poke-the-mans-753683843

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.
